column5: Got out for Goose opener Thursday.  They weren't flying a bunch but we got a few    they cooked just fine in the slow cooker     Then Satuday we headed out for eyes..pretty slow fishing but managed a nice smallie     end of the day got us a double header of walleyes about 22 inches     After that, Sunday and Monday was about a thousand km of driving to get my son back to school
Don't you just love fishing in socks!  Nice fish.
Good show.  Going out for bunnies tomorrow, can't wait for chicken season.  I'd love to get into goose hunting, I sure love to eat em.
Don't you just love fishing in socks!  Nice fish.   That looks like some great eats there. Nice shoot,n and hook,n.

Nice Shooting Dara!!  As if I wasn't already  pumped up enough for goose opener down here!!  I have a feeling it will be slow this year.  The farmers where I hunt aren't seeing many birds this year.  They thinks it's because of the heat.  But I'm not sure.

Hey Nick. I seen a real nice flock Sunday near cold water. Talking to a guy that hunts up there alot ,was saying the farmers are turning thier fields already. I have noticed though here in the bay, the duck population is growing real fast. I am down there at dark in the mornings and just sit there listening to them quacking away. Gets the old hunting blood going. Yes I know Im just teasing myself as I wont be shooting any.LOL
It was just too hot to keep the shoes on in the boat, even the hunting was pretty warm, but that's early season. Next weekend chickens will be open. Hopefully it cools off a bit this year
